sec.p:
Where individual local authorities in the UK define a pavement defect by size (depth or height), this tends to be in the region of 15 to 25 mm to be a potential hazard and is thus prioritised for repair;

If a defect is more than 20 mm deep it will be considered hazardous and our inspector will mark it with yellow paint. Defects that are less than 20 mm deep wouldn’t normally be considered a hazard.26

The Council regularly inspects its footways for defects where levels vary by 15 mm or more.27
